verbs.description: [V: rose] brings nothing to the table letter to the editor i watched with heightened interest the debate between congressman donovan and max rose especially since i knew little about the latter after an hour my primary takeaway is rose should n’t garner even a single vote by anyone with objectivity his major claim was that he was a service veteran … over and over again as if that merits his being elected many in my family served and saw action in uniform rarely speaking about their time in uniform because that time was not used as a crutch for the rest of their lives most revealing was that rose inchoate grasp of transportation was embarrassingly off the mark pushing south shore fast ferry … islanders do n’t want it it was tried after sandy at great kills gateway and lacked ridership despite free parking nearby nycedc conducted a study about a decade ago indicating low forecasted ridership he clearly did n’t research this topic donovan nailed it indicating the north shore busway and the west shore light rail are what we need rose keeps saying that he wants to drain the swamp in both parties i shudder to think of this misinformed outcast in congress already having made enemies everywhere he would north shore congress dan washington steven p scalici sandy the table earnse bay rose nycedc max rose congressman donovan steven p scalici editor congressman west shore
